Attitude towards handling conflicts

When conflicts arise in a relationship, men and women handle them very differently. Men often choose to avoid the issue; they dislike facing complex emotional problems and prefer to respond with silence. Like when faced with a storm, they retreat into their own "cave" to ponder solutions alone. This escapist attitude often confuses and frustrates women, making them feel that men don't care about their feelings.

Women, on the other hand, actively seek solutions, hoping to resolve conflicts through communication. They express their thoughts and feelings, hoping men will understand them. However, men's silence often exacerbates women's emotions, leading to a further escalation of the conflict. Surveys show that nearly 60% of couples experience escalated conflicts due to differences in how men and women handle situations.

